a wonderful christmas day in new york.ai_text:
I was standing outside the hotel window
When the sun came up one christmas morning;

The city was just awake like an actress
Upon the stage a block from the door;

And then I saw a man step out quite pale
And he was carrying a small old chest.

He paused for a second, looking about,
And then he walked down the street a bit,

And the man looked in the chest and he stared;
And then he was running--and then he flew.
